Technology Brief:
   GM Unit Sets Pacts
   For Supply of Parts
   Of Satellite TV System
Thomson, which plans to invest $50 million to produce the
system, has an exclusive agreement with Hughes to produce the
satellite dishes and decoder boxes for 18 months, or until
one million units are sold, whichever comes first once
DirectTv begins operating in early 1994. The system is
expected to retail for about $700.
   News Datacom, a British maker of antipirating devices and
a subsidiary of Rupert Murdoch's News Corp., will provide the
encryption devices for the system. Terms of its investment
weren't disclosed.
   Hughes Communications is a unit of General Motors Corp.